Date: Tue, 22 Dec 2015 21:48:51 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] Conform to PEP 0394 in Python sources

In order to tolerate differences across platforms, all new code that
needs to invoke the Python interpreter should not specify python,
but rather should specify either python2 or python3
---
 configure | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/configure b/configure
index 23edb6b..3a79deb 100755
--- a/configure
+++ b/configure
@@ -1,4 +1,4 @@
-#!/usr/bin/env python
+#!/usr/bin/env python2
 
 # This source file is part of the Swift.org open source project
 #
